   <concept id="FAR_12_505" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">12.505</ph> Applicability of certain
laws to contracts for the acquisition of COTS items.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d740e8" class="- topic/p ">COTS items are a subset of commercial products. Therefore,
any laws listed in sections <xref href="12.503.dita#FAR_12_503"
                  base="i1112774"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">12.503</xref> and <xref href="12.504.dita#FAR_12_504"
                  base="i1112857"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">12.504</xref> are also inapplicable
or modified in their applicability to contracts or subcontracts
for the acquisition of COTS items. In addition, the following laws
are not applicable to contracts for the acquisition of COTS items:</p>
         <ol id="d713e28" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d740e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d713e38" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d740e23">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The portion
of <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?path=/prelim@title41/subtitle4/chapter83&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 8302</xref> , American
Materials Required for Public Use, paragraph (a)(1) that reads “substantially
all from articles, materials, or supplies mined, produced, or manufactured
in the United States,” Buy American—Supplies, domestic content test,
except as provided in <xref href="25.101.dita#FAR_25_101"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.101</xref>(a)(2)(ii) (see <xref href="52.225-1.dita#FAR_52_225_1"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.225-1</xref> and <xref href="52.225-3.dita#FAR_52_225_3"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.225-3</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d740e40">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>The portion
of <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?path=/prelim@title41/subtitle4/chapter83&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 8303</xref>, Contracts
for Public Works, paragraph (a)(2) that reads “substantially all
from articles, materials, or supplies mined, produced, or manufactured
in the United States,” Buy American—Construction Materials, domestic
content test, except as provided in <xref href="25.201.dita#FAR_25_201"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.201</xref>(b)(2)(ii)(see <xref href="52.225-9.dita#FAR_52_225_9"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.225-9</xref> and <xref href="52.225-11.dita#FAR_52_225_11"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.225-11</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d740e57">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section69&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">42 U.S.C. 69</xref> 62(c)(3)(A),
Certification and Estimate of Percentage of Recovered Material.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d740e64">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Compliance
Plan and Certification Requirement, section 1703 of the National
Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2013 (Pub. L. 112-239),
Title XVII, Ending trafficking in Government Contracting (see <xref href="52.222-50.dita#FAR_52_222_50"
                        base="i1056535"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-50</xref>(h) and <xref href="52.222-56.dita#FAR_52_222_56"
                        base="i1056889"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-56</xref>).</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
